Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on the design of a MAC protocol for cognitive radio networks.
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is also likely as the paper proposes a mathematical model to analyze the throughput performance of the proposed protocol.
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is a possible category as the paper may discuss security issues related to cognitive radio networks.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possible category as the paper may discuss the control aspects of the proposed protocol.
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is a less likely category as the paper does not explicitly mention multimedia, but it may be relevant if the proposed protocol is used for multimedia applications.
